post_survey.music_making: I'm not a musician. I wish!
post_survey.medium: Spotify, media, other streaming sites, and some owned/downloaded
post_survey.activities: Almost anything. Working, writing, drawing, gaming, doing chores, showering, taking a walk--all better with music.
post_survey.habit_change: They haven't changed too much, except for the way I discover some new music to listen to. Nowadays I mostly discover new (or just new to me) music by browsing Spotify. When I was a kid, I largely discovered new music (including my core, favorite artists) by listening to the radio and checking out CDs from my local library. And, of course, by playing video games. Which hasn't changed.
post_survey.habits: I just about covered it, I think. I love music and listen to it all the time. And I truly listen to a wide variety of things. It's possible for almost any genre to have something pleasant in it.
